{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -c 'rg -n \"caclulator|calculator|inference-conference|project-image--calc|img|video|source src\" frontend/index.html frontend/*.html'","aggregated_output":"frontend/calculator-writeup.html:7:<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Why an AI VRAM calculator — not a todo list — is the right target for an agent loop that writes frontend code.\">\nfrontend/calculator-writeup.html:225:    <a class=\"site-link\" href=\"https://aideploymentcalculator.vercel.app/\">Try the calculator &rarr;</a>\nfrontend/calculator-writeup.html:231:    <p class=\"sub\">I built an AI VRAM calculator in TypeScript to test frontend agent loops. It was the right kind of mistake.</p>\nfrontend/calculator-writeup.html:240:    <p class=\"lead\">I built an AI VRAM calculator because I needed a sample app for TypeScript frontend loops. That turned out to be the right kind of mistake: calculators force generated frontends to deal with real state, real math, real copy, and real edge cases.</p>\nfrontend/calculator-writeup.html:242:    <p>The app is live at <a href=\"https://aideploymentcalculator.vercel.app/\">aideploymentcalculator.vercel.app</a>. You give it a model size, precision, workload, and deployment mode; it gives you a VRAM estimate, a hardware tier, a rough speed, and the assumptions it used to get there. Everything runs in the browser. There is no backend.</p>\nfrontend/calculator-writeup.html:269:    <p>Good frontend agent loops need a product-shaped target: something with state that interacts, math that can be checked, copy that carries meaning, and users who would notice. A calculator is a cheat code &mdash; the domain supplies the rigor, and the loop either meets it or fails visibly.</p>\nfrontend/calculator-writeup.html:274:    The calculator is live at <a href=\"https://aideploymentcalculator.vercel.app/\"><strong>aideploymentcalculator.vercel.app</strong></a>; source at <a href=\"https://github.com/rxdt/ai_deployment_calculator\">rxdt/ai_deployment_calculator</a>. The harness it hardened: <a href=\"https://github.com/rxdt/loopgate-harness\">rxdt/loopgate-harness</a>.\nfrontend/index.html:59:        \"url\": \"https://aideploymentcalculator.vercel.app/\",\nfrontend/index.html:322:      .portrait img {\nfrontend/index.html:415:      .project-image--calc {\nfrontend/index.html:434:      .project-image--calc:hover {\nfrontend/index.html:451:      .project-video {\nfrontend/index.html:594:        .portrait img {\nfrontend/index.html:654:          <img src=\"/assets/merged.gif\" alt=\"Animated portrait of Rox dT\" />\nfrontend/index.html:667:                href=\"https://aideploymentcalculator.vercel.app/\"\nfrontend/index.html:670:                <img\nfrontend/index.html:672:                  src=\"/assets/caclulator.png\"\nfrontend/index.html:680:                  A calculator to size AI deployments before buying hardware. It\nfrontend/index.html:686:                    ><a href=\"https://aideploymentcalculator.vercel.app/\"\nfrontend/index.html:690:                  <a href=\"calculator-writeup.html\">Writeup</a>\nfrontend/index.html:693:                    href=\"https://github.com/rxdt/ai_deployment_calculator\"\nfrontend/index.html:717:                <img\nfrontend/index.html:759:                <video\nfrontend/index.html:760:                  class=\"project-image project-video\"\nfrontend/index.html:766:                  <source src=\"/assets/comfyday-sample.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\" />\nfrontend/index.html:767:                </video>\nfrontend/index.html:805:                <img\nfrontend/index.html:807:                  src=\"/assets/inference-conference.png\"\nfrontend/index.html:59:        \"url\": \"https://aideploymentcalculator.vercel.app/\",\nfrontend/index.html:322:      .portrait img {\nfrontend/index.html:415:      .project-image--calc {\nfrontend/index.html:434:      .project-image--calc:hover {\nfrontend/index.html:451:      .projec